The article discusses the importance of national preparedness in the face of various challenges, including natural disasters, climate change, and infectious diseases like COVID-19. The author emphasizes the need for the United States to take bold action to address the dangers posed by climate change, invest in weather forecasting and climate research, and upgrade infrastructure to be more resilient. The article also highlights the commitment to global climate action, including rejoining the Paris Climate Agreement. The importance of vaccination against COVID-19 is stressed, along with the recognition of the bravery and sacrifices of first responders. The author calls on individuals and communities to prepare themselves and protect against immediate crises and their residual effects. National Preparedness Month is proclaimed as a call to action for all sectors of society to work together to enhance resilience and readiness.